crave /kreɪv/

(craving,craved,craves) 

1. V-T If you crave something, you want to have it very much. 渴望得到 

例： There may be certain times of day when smokers crave their cigarette. 一天中可能有那么几次吸烟者特别想叼上烟。 

2. craving N-COUNT 渴求 

例： ...a craving for sugar. …对糖的渴求。

